00:12:45.900 --> 00:12:49.410
as our third issue as we look at risk.

268
00:12:49.410 --> 00:12:53.610
Now, in order to calculate these three dimensions,

269
00:12:53.610 --> 00:12:56.583
you have to look at a disease outcome against an exposure.

270
00:12:58.620 --> 00:13:00.610
Now here's the first two by two table

271
00:13:02.400 --> 00:13:04.920
or contingency table.

272
00:13:04.920 --> 00:13:06.840
If you're going to use the equations

273
00:13:06.840 --> 00:13:09.423
in that first table that I presented,

274
00:13:11.370 --> 00:13:15.390
you need to set up your two by two table like that.

275
00:13:15.390 --> 00:13:18.750
On the y-axis will be the disease or outcome,

276
00:13:18.750 --> 00:13:21.333
and on the x-axis will be the exposure.

277
00:13:22.800 --> 00:13:23.633
Okay?

278
00:13:25.170 --> 00:13:26.340
So relative risk,

279
00:13:26.340 --> 00:13:28.920
you could have an increase or a decrease, of course.

280
00:13:28.920 --> 00:13:29.753
Absolute risk,

281
00:13:29.753 --> 00:13:31.350
you could have an increase or a decrease.

282
00:13:31.350 --> 00:13:34.470
And then there's the number needed to treat.

